MIDWAY MISCHIEF hounded the frontrunner down the backside on the outside, battled for the lead midway on the turn two off the fence and faltered between foes in upper stretch. OCTOBER FROST was in tight on the rail nearing the five eighths pole, was steadied, trailed the field afterwards and could not recover enough after that to pose a threat in the stretch drive.
